## Summary of Implementation Approaches

| Method | Use Case | Complexity | State Management |
|--------|----------|------------|------------------|
| Basic Auth | Simple APIs | Low | Stateless |
| Form Login | Web Applications | Medium | Session-based |
| JWT | REST APIs | High | Stateless |
| OAuth2/OIDC | Social Login | High | Token-based |
| LDAP | Enterprise Apps | Medium | Session-based |
| Method Security | Fine-grained Control | Medium | Flexible |
| Database Auth | Custom User Management | Medium | Session-based |
| Reactive Security | Non-blocking Apps | High | Flexible |

Each method serves different use cases and can be combined based on application requirements. The choice depends on factors like application type, scalability needs, user management complexity, and integration requirements.

